The paper deals with the analysis of the generalized second price (GSP) auction for sponsored search, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of game theory (cs.GT), information retrieval (cs.IR), and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the efficiency and equilibrium properties of the auction, which are topics in economics and mechanism design (cs.EC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
